title: UK to start evacuating diplomats from Sudan after clashes in Khartoum
description: The UK will evacuate British diplomats from Sudan as soon as possible but other British nationals are being advised to stay put, despite deadly fighting in the capital, it is understood.

title: British woman trapped by deadly clashes tells of harrowing ordeal
description: A British-Sudanese woman has described her "harrowing" ordeal over the last seven days in the capital Khartoum during clashes that have resulted in hundreds of deaths.

title: Two dead and 10 injured in restaurant fire 'started by waiter flambeing food'
description: Two people have died and another 10 have been injured in Madrid after a restaurant fire - believed to have been started by a waiter flambeing a dish.

title: Thailand issues 'don't go out' warning as heat index hits record 54C
description: People in Bangkok and other areas of Thailand have been warned not to go outside due to extreme heat.

title: UK nationals to be evacuated from Sudan, head of Sudanese army says
description: The UK will evacuate diplomats and nationals from Sudan, the head of the Sudanese army says.

title: US Supreme Court preserves women's access to abortion pill
description: Women's access to a widely used abortion pill in the US has been maintained by the Supreme Court during an ongoing legal battle over the drug.

title: Sudan clashes continue despite ceasefire: Here's what's happening on the ground
description: Intense violence continues to rock Sudan a week after fighting first erupted between its army and the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) paramilitary force.
